1
00:00:00,879 --> 00:00:03,416
I know that there's an invasive species
that's entered the glades...

2
00:00:03,417 --> 00:00:07,544
And now is the time for us to rise up!

3
00:00:08,982 --> 00:00:11,162
And i'll do anything to protect my family.

4
00:00:12,140 --> 00:00:14,629
Who can tell me what this word means?

5
00:00:14,661 --> 00:00:16,007
She's a very special girl, sir.

6
00:00:16,008 --> 00:00:18,147
Yes, she is. she's also a very young one.

7
00:00:18,148 --> 00:00:21,534
Hey, deputy. If you can hear me,
raise your hand.

8
00:00:21,535 --> 00:00:22,516
Oh, my god.

9
00:00:24,690 --> 00:00:25,920
The lights came in during the hurricane, right?

10
00:00:25,920 --> 00:00:28,260
So wouldn't it stand to reason
if you were a hybrid psychopath

11
00:00:28,260 --> 00:00:31,362
planning an invasion, you might do it
under the cover of a storm?

12
00:00:33,350 --> 00:00:34,323
Szura's gone, Russell.

13
00:00:34,323 --> 00:00:37,690
I don't know what he's planning,
but i'm gonna need your help to stop him.

14
00:00:37,690 --> 00:00:39,443
- Thank you, miss.
- You're welcome.

15
00:00:39,443 --> 00:00:43,018
It's nice to know if i get in trouble again,
you're always nearby.

16
00:00:45,492 --> 00:00:46,501
<i>That's right, Paul.</i>

17
00:00:46,501 --> 00:00:49,132
<i>winds are moving northwest
at 12 miles per hour,</i>

18
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:50,671
<i>and Accutrack is predicting that miranda</i>

19
00:00:50,671 --> 00:00:53,357
<i>could make landfall as early as 8:00
tomorrow night.</i>

20
00:00:53,361 --> 00:00:54,341
<i>Well, Larkin, we're hearing up here</i>

21
00:00:54,341 --> 00:00:55,922
<i>that some residents of west palm beach</i>

22
00:00:55,922 --> 00:00:58,581
<i>- are already evacuating.
- That's my understanding, as well,</i>

23
00:00:58,581 --> 00:01:00,555
<i>but even though the national weather service</i>

24
00:01:00,563 --> 00:01:02,317
<i>is saying that we'll all be safe down here,</i>

25
00:01:02,323 --> 00:01:04,901
<i>i would caution all Homestead residents</i>

26
00:01:04,901 --> 00:01:06,882
<i>to be prepared for anything.</i>

27
00:01:06,882 --> 00:01:08,282
<i>Well, certainly, better safe than sorry,</i>

28
00:01:08,282 --> 00:01:10,452
<i>but right now, i think we can all be grateful</i>

29
00:01:10,452 --> 00:01:12,962
<i>that this time it looks like we dodged a bullet.</i>

30
00:01:12,962 --> 00:01:14,661
<i>That's definitely one way of looking at it.</i>

31
00:01:14,661 --> 00:01:16,588
<i>Thanks, Paul.
Back to you.</i>

